  "text": "Results are shown here for a 6-yr simulation of CAM3 using the finite volume dynamical core at 2°ϫ 2.5°horizontal resolution. The revisions to the cloud treatment in CAM3 have warmed the tropical tropopause and virtually eliminated the CPT bias in CAM3 with respect to GPS/MET, as shown in Fig. 6 . However, recalling that the GPS/MET observations are for a particularly cold year at the CPT [CITATION_1] , CAM3 probably still has a small cold bias. The simulation is nearly unchanged over South America and the Atlantic. Across the Indian and Pacific Oceans the CPT is 2-3 K warmer. The CPT remains slightly cold in JJA because CAM3 does not have sufficient vertical resolution to represent the seasonal cycle of the tropopause pressure. Tests have confirmed that the tropopause descends and warms in JJA if the vertical grid spacing is decreased to ϳ500 m.",
